## Walkabout
Walkabout was an OSINT/puzzle run task, where the challenge began by receiving a QR code. Each QR code gave a hint to the next location and the flag would be at the final destination.  



### Challenge Description
```
Find the location presented when scanning the QR-code, you will find the flag at the final location.

![QR image](data:image/png;base64,)
```

## Final destination
The last image did not contain a picture of a location, but a picture of "the city's best kebab since 1984". Being born and raised in the city I have had my fair share of the local food, and luckily for me, this particular place I have done a thorough research of beforhand. Here google reverse image would have told you that this image belongs to the kebab shop "Dronningens Kebab" famous for their well... kebab.  
<details>
  <summary>Click to view the image</summary>
  <img src="final_location.jpg" alt="Final location" width="400"/>
</details>

\
A fun fact about this particular shop is that it recently moved location. Below is were it used to be, close to Oslo Domkirke. 

<details>
  <summary>Click to view the image</summary>
  <img src="kebab_shop_old_location.PNG" alt="Old kebab shop location" width="400"/>
</details>

\
But the current location is here: 32 Skippergata (thank me later). A google search would have showed you the new address, but the attached google picture might show the old location (at the time of the CTF that appeared to be the case)

This turned out to be a game changer, as we had been passed by other teams at this point, but when we went to the old location we suddenly remembered that it had moved, and ended up getting first blood because of this. Red square marks where the last QR code was found.
